President Barack Obama has announced his intention to nominate Ward Brehm for the position of Member, Board of Directors of the African Development Foundation. Brehm is the founder and chairman of The Brehm Group, Inc., an estate planning/life insurance consulting firm. He previously served as chairman of the United States African Development Foundation from 2004 to 2008. Brehm has also been involved in various projects in Africa, including the Windpump Project in Kenya and the founding of Equal World Coffee, which supports Rwandan farmers. He has received recognition for his work, including the Presidential Citizenship Medal, and has authored two books on his experiences in Africa.